- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is the most likely category as the paper deals with online abuse and its impact on UK MPs, which is a topic related to the intersection of technology and society. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a likely category as the paper analyzes patterns of abuse on social media platforms. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) could be a relevant category as the paper may discuss the development of tools or algorithms to detect and prevent online abuse. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) could be a relevant category as the paper may discuss the security and privacy implications of online abuse. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) could be a relevant category as the paper may analyze the language used in online abuse and its impact on the targeted individuals.
